text: Val de Lambronne is a commune of 185 people (2017). It is in the region Occitanie in the Aude department in the south of France. The municipality was created on 1 January 2016 and consists of the former communes of Caudeval (the seat) and Gueytes-et-Labastide.Arrêté préfectoral 12 November 2015 == References == ==Other websites== Category:2016 establishments in France Category:Communes in Aude
title: Val de Lambronne
